                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 17px; line-height: normal">The Enchanter Manifesto</span>
<br />
                <span style="font-size: 16px; line-height: normal"><span style="font-style: italic">Enchanter Letter 13</span></span></span>
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: BLUE"><span style="font-weight: bold">HAPPY HOLIDAYS!</span> and Welcome to Enchanter Letter 13, Im Nanyea The Wayward of the Stormhammer server and a proud member of Township Rebellion. For you first time readers, remember the primary usefulness of this thread is as a forum for you to agree or disagree or offer useful and constructive suggestions about what you think of EQ and where it should go in the future.</span>
<br />

<br />
Enchanters are doing pretty well at the moment, and we are all excited to see how our melee brethen take to the new system.  Encouraged also by the fact that it gives classes a way to expand besides just AAs and straight spells.  Wish our melee friends the best with their new discs and hope they start to lay the foundation for their revamp.  But of course there are enchanter concerns in EQ, which the first part of this letter shall attempt to lay out.
<br />
<span style="color: red">
<br />
*Crowd Control in LDON raids*</span>
<br />
-currently chanters are getting mowed down and the resist rates on the hard <span style="font-weight: bold">RAIDS</span> make it impractical to mez at all in favor of slowing down pulls and bringing smaller groups of mobs.  Please look into this and make adjustments where neccesary
<br />
<span style="color: red">*XP penalites for charm*</span>
<br />
-Theres still some concern about pets and xp in groups, I think it would be equitable fix if the agro rules (ie 4+ on agro list) be implemented as far as xp to minimize the penalty taken by pet in gruops to 1% vs using the scaled system currently in use.
<br />
<span style="color: red">*Bulwark of Alendar and Umbra Spelllines*</span>
<br />
Bulwark is a nice spell, but VERY limited in usefullness, a possible way to increase the desireability of this spell would be to expand it to include the damage per tick from DOTS, whereas umbra line is all but worthless and a waste of a buff, we would like to see this line re-evaluated and changed to be a useful self buff.
<br />

<br />
<span style="color: indigo">But where do we go from here... we've slain the gods themselves...??? Why a NEW expansion, but what will it be about?!!!</span>
<br />

<br />
From here on out we will call the next Expansion Gates of Discord (GoD!) and will primarily be focusing on the roles and how they change with the expected new levels and 100+aa points of new skills.  Like all expansions with level increases or LARGE AA increases this will dramatically effect the game, especially so in terms of old content.  <span style="font-weight: bold">THATS OK THOUGH!</span> because old content is just that... old.  
<br />

<br />
So Anyhow here are the issues we expect in the future expansion, with a little bit of what we would like to see:
<br />

<br />
1) ways to mitigate avoid damage 
<br />

<br />
*group rune 1500 to group 
<br />
*Bulwark of Alendar to include DOT damage 
<br />
*revamp of shadow/umbra line for avoidance/mana regen 
<br />
*high level self buff (we have shielding, druzzil, umbra, clarity, bulwark... combine these into a self buff to replace either focus or brells.. include a shielding or avoidance mod) 
<br />

<br />
2) enhanced CC 
<br />
To give chanters back the edge in CC will need 
<br />
*lower mana cost mez 
<br />
*more of a lure component via AA or via spell, its too dangerous on some LDON raids making it impractical 
<br />
*longer duration mez 
<br />
**possibly a curse based lure mez, that cant be dispelled 8 min refresh, 10 min duration Max of whatever level trash mobs are in next expansion (probly 70-73) make it stack with reg mez (key here is refresh needs to be fast enough to perma mez something and go to bathroom, while at the same time slow enough that you wont replace normal spell mezzes) 
<br />
*single target stun, fast cast high cap (level 70 8-10 secs + something... like mana drain or dispel, low resist) 
<br />

<br />
3) raid utility 
<br />
*v3 overhaste 
<br />
*v3 imp spell damage buff (pair it with something else useful and a manadot or increased mana cost) 
<br />
*group deagro spell 
<br />
*pair a nuke with insanity 1300-1500 damage (30-50 lure component)
<br />

<br />
Some other Ideas that chanters have been tossing around and would like a lil consideration given too...
<br />

<br />
*a better debuff, we like tash, but its just not scaling with the increasing MR of mobs and the improved debuffs of other classes
<br />

<br />
along with this link <a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=12891#12891" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">here</span></a> for AA suggestions or this <a href="http://www.therunes.net/forums/viewtopic.php?p=12892#12892" target="_blank" class="postlink"><span style="font-weight: bold">Link</span></a> for spell suggestions.
<br />

<br />
Anyhow as always feel free to leave comments or suggestions as this is the PRIMARY purpose of this letter, and maybe secretly to weasel my way into a beta or three.
<br />

<br />
DISCUSS
<br />

<br />
serverwide.enchanter
<br />

