                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Nice letter Nanyea...
<br />

<br />
Totally agree that Bulwark needs looked at.. and if nothing else, if Bulwark stays the same, please get rid of the lame component cost and lower the recast on it. Changing it to include dot dmg would kick arse, but again, would make to many PoTime encounters and lower encounters way to easy. Clerics dont need components to do melee mitigation, but we do for the much less needed spell mitigation?
<br />

<br />
Umbra.. total waste of a spell atm, never was scaled up, and a +dodge% mod on it would at least make it semi useful again and/or make it the self mana regen buff we've all been dreaming about since zealot/familiars/phantom/lich/etc showed their faces.
<br />

<br />
Ldon raid mobs need their MR's checked, or we need a magic lure based Mez just to survive these encounters. 
<br />

<br />
Please no group rune, as much as I love the idea, just imagine the aggro, and you also trivialize a LOT of AE-DD encounters just by having a ton of enchanters, and chain runing my group for an entire fight seems like it would not be fun.  My job is to CC/buff/debuff/nuke, not to keep my group alive cause my cleric wants to melee and i can just "rune us all". Group form of Bulwark.. now that has a little more merit, saves time, mana and a chitload of peri's.
<br />

<br />
Currently Focus (the spell that overwrites our crappy shield line) adds 544hp, 75str, 70dex..  shielding adds 350hp, 39ac, and 40mr.  And in all rights, i dont know any enchanters/casters that perfer shielding's ac/mr to the extra 200ish hp from the Focus line..  Adding 100-200hp to shielding, a +%shielding, or a mana regen (although, we are the ONLY class that needs a self mana regen, the others all have a form of it outside their shield lines) might give me reason to dust it off. But as of current, the spell wastes space in my book unless I really really need MR. Dont think they should add ALL the stuff to it that Nanyea suggested, then it would start to be come a little overpower (really fun though!). 
<br />

<br />
Love the CC ideas. Although a long term mez, while would be great for the bladder, would suck for game dynamics, because you know a ton of mobs would suddenly get the no mez flag. 
<br />

<br />
Overhaste sounds great, bards would kill us. Group de-aggro, no thanks, I'm busy nuff on raids without having to mgb deaggro the raid or the cleric group. 
<br />

<br />
Improved spell dmg is something we DON'T need. I know. sounds bad. i love nuking, and i enjoy helping kill stuff at raids, and i feel like crap when i get so proud of my 2500pt crit and the wizard laughs in my face. BUT on an average mob (normal MR, some i can't do squat) i can pump out 40-50k in dmg chaining insanity and dementing visions. thats not to damn shabby for a pud enchanter. Wizards are doing 175-220k ish and i dont have an issue with that, but add up all the xtra dps from c5 mana regen, haste and our pretty pretty pets (go go 20dps) and you'll see we arent overall that far behind in dmg dealing. Just because you dont see the pretty numbers on the screen doesnt mean you arent making a HELL of a difference overall. I'll have to admit i'd love a less resisted nuke, maybe 1kish lure nuke. Something that we can use on those annoying mobs, but not powerful enough to totally displace our main line. 
<br />

<br />
Tash - needs fixed please. it fell behind a long time ago and is only really useful anymore as a gateway debuff to help others land theirs and to allow us to nuke. Nobody uses MR based nukes anymore cept us and clerics.
<br />

