                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not a problem, I just think that we have too much mana as it is. Mind you, I am speaking from an 'end game' perspective. Granted, I do keep in mind that not everyone plays the end game and some are casual players or are still working on making it to the end game content.
<br />

<br />
No matter what the situation may be I think there should be a risk while you progress to whatever your goal may be. At one point in time we had low hp/ low mana etc. and we made due. The ench would run oom and shit would hit the fan. (I am talking pre-KEI days) Even in some situations I can run lom but I honestly have not used Gather Mana in months, not even when I die. 
<br />

<br />
I prefer chaos over comfort and I think that giving more mana regen would bring more comfort to the game which it has enough now as it is. Of course this is just how I prefer to play but honestly, what is the fun when there is hardly any risk left. 
<br />

<br />
The Enchanter class is about in line as it should be. We do not need more power, maybe a few minor adjustments and that is fine. About the only things I would enjoy seeing changed would be things that I personally find to be more beneficial versus enjoyable. 
<br />
I'd like to see changes with -
<br />
Tash
<br />
Cripple (New Spell)
<br />
Lagarns/Whirl (New Spell)
<br />
Boggle (I think any changes would be nice at this point. Comparing it to the Jolt line of spells, I think it is only fair that it 'works as intended')
<br />
Asphyx (May as well up that one too)
<br />

<br />
As far as items go, I'd like to see a long shitty quest thrown out as a way for enchanters to get an item similar to 'Memory' (statless would be fine) clickable from inventory. It was and still is a highly desired and useful item that has the most craptastic drop rate ever known. 
<br />

<br />
*Someone mentioned above something about rapture. I always hated that spell, I don't want another. If a long duration mes is that highly-desired, I'd much rather see it in the form of an AA vs a spell.
<br />

<br />
Edit: ps/ wtf is the Innoruuk's Irony Augment? (Guk?  <img src="images/smiles/icon_lol.gif" alt="icon_lol.gif" border="0" /> )</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=158777" target="_blank" class="postlink">Ravvenn</a>
