                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">hey add me to the signatories.
<br />

<br />
i don't agree with a lot of the above.  however something needs to be done to either refocus the chanter as a class or if the goal is to dilute the original class skills out as they have been, then dilute some of the other classes powers over to the chanters.
<br />

<br />
our skills/spells have been given to so many other classes over the years it now seems everybody does something better than we used to do it.
<br />

<br />
we're no longer top of the line in haste, or slow, or mana regen (not that thanks to KEI we ever cast a mana regen in a group post 45th anymore).  and as of 53rd we suffer serious issues with mezzing and charming mobs of an equal or higher level making crowd control very hard.  i mean think about it, a level 58 chanter can't do anything other than root a level 58 mob for crowd control.  something like 5 other classes can do that, and they all get to wear real armor!  mean while anytime we figure out how to solo BLAM! out comes the nerf stick.
<br />

<br />
anyway, i don't claim to have an answer.  i think most of the responces above are too focused on one aspect or another of the class.  i think it's about time SoE and the dev team look at the class and re-think the purpose of the class.  cause let's face it, one more drop only useless illusion and collectively every person who's ever loved playing an enchanter is gonna keel over and puke.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />**************************************
<br />
