                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think much needs to be done to the class in my opinion.  Maybe some little tweaks to a few spells but thats about it.  
<br />

<br />
My Ideas,
<br />
Umbra : Up AC by 10 and add a +5 spellshield to it.  There is never a time I will have Virtue over Po9+Kaazad.
<br />

<br />
Boggle: I really have no problem with this spell other then it costs way to much mana.  It for the most part works when I need it.
<br />

<br />
Sleep: Ok I use Bliss instead of sleep most of the time, so I say change sleep to an AE mezz.  Not PBAE like WoM but a real AE Mezz with currently restriced level.  Give it a max of 4 mobs, it will trivalize some content but the level cap and max mobs will keep it in check.
<br />

<br />
Tranq/VoQ:  Well since there is already a VoQ single target spell with LDoN its kinda hard to say what I would do with Tranq.  Though I would like the durations either to match KEI or for KEI to be nerfed.  Maybe make KEI single target Tranq group KEI something along them lines cause right now Tranq is pointless.
<br />

<br />
SoM: Add a +dodge mod to it.  Not just to enchanters version but to all versions for all INT casters. 
<br />

<br />
I'd like to see an AA Memblur like the bard fading memories aa.  Out of all the cross classing stuff I thought that was really stupid to give bards one of the only enchanter only ablities.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: red"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=553015" target="_blank" class="postlink">Caterbie Da'Fish</a></span>
